# Artwork API

## Authentication [/api/v1/auth]

### Register New User [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    {
        "username": "newuser",
        "password": "password123"
    }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    "User created successfully"

### Login User [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    {
        "username": "newuser",
        "password": "password123"
    }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    {
        "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
        "roles": ["ROLE_USER"]
    }

> Note: The returned `token` must be included in the `Authorization` header (`Bearer <token>`) for all protected endpoints.

## Artwork Collection [/api/v1/artworks]

### Get All Artworks [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Artwork])
    
> Requires JWT token. Roles allowed: `ROLE_USER`, `ROLE_ADMIN`.

### Create New Artwork [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    {
        "id": 1,
        "title": "Artwork Title",
        "artist": "Artist Name",
        "description": "Artwork Description",
        "art_type": "Artwork Type",
        "thumbnail": "Image URL"
    }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

> Requires JWT token. Roles allowed: `ROLE_ADMIN`.

## Single Artwork [/api/v1/artworks/{id}]

### Get Artwork by ID [GET]
+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (Integer, required) - Artwork ID

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    {
        "id": 1,
        "title": "Artwork Title",
        "artist": "Artist Name",
        "description": "Artwork Description",
        "art_type": "Artwork Type",
        "thumbnail": "Image URL"
    }

> Requires JWT token. Roles allowed: `ROLE_USER`, `ROLE_ADMIN`.

### Update Artwork by ID [PUT]
+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (Integer, required) - Artwork ID

+ Request (application/json)
    {
        "title": "Artwork Title",
        "artist": "Artist Name",
        "description": "Artwork Description",
        "art_type": "Artwork Type",
        "thumbnail": "Image URL"
    }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

> Requires JWT token. Roles allowed: `ROLE_ADMIN`.

### Delete Artwork by ID [DELETE]
+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (Integer, required) - Artwork ID

+ Response 204 (application/json)

> Requires JWT token. Roles allowed: `ROLE_ADMIN`.

# Data Structures

## Artwork (object)
+ id: 1 (Integer)
+ title: "Mona Lisa" (String)
+ artist: "Leonardo da Vinci" (String)
+ description: "Woman painting" (String)
+ art_type: "Painting" (String)
+ thumbnail: "Image URL" (String)

## User (object)
+ id: MongoDB ObjectID (String)
+ username: "user1" (String)
+ password: "password123" (String)
+ roles: "[ROLE_USER]" (List<String>)
